Executive Profile
Bradley D. Goskowicz  Chief Executive Officer and President, Microbiologics Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.61--
Background

		Mr. Bradley D. Goskowicz, also known as Brad, has been the President of Microbiologics Inc. since March 2010 and serves as its Chief Executive Officer. Mr. Goskowicz joined MicroBioLogics in February of 2009 as the Chief Marketing Officer, where he has led the market launch of EZ-Accu Shotï¿½ and other key marketing initiatives. Mr. Goskowicz served as Vice President of Marketing at ABIOMED, Inc. He served in senior sales, marketing and leadership positions with companies ... such as Johnson & Johnson, Medtronic, Inc. and Thoratec Corporation. He served as Vice President of Sales & Marketing at Thoratec Corp. from January 2001 to January 2005. He served as Vice President of Marketing and Clinical Site Development of Myocor, Inc. In addition, Mr. Goskowicz served as President of US Speedskating for the last four years. He has been Director-At-Large at Aoac International since October 2013. He served as Independent Director of MOCON Inc. from December 3, 2012 to June 22, 2017. He has been a Director at American Association For Laboratory Accreditation since January 2014.Read Full Background




